The paper discusses a generative model called Exponential-family harmoniums (EFHs) that can be trained with unsupervised learning techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent EFHs, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of EFHs in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which suggests that it may be relevant to these sub-categories as well.
